        "display_name" : "Steven the Easily Amused",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1655780/steven-the-easily-amused"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1475276649,
      "post_id" : 5251352,
      "comment_id" : 66894863,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "On Centos / RHL This is what I prefer to find the JDK (if installed)  <code>find &#47;usr&#47;java -wholename &#39;*ava&#47;jdk*&#39; -prune</code>  But behavior depends whether you are talking about  OpenJDK or Oracle Java and how it was installed in the first place."
    } ],
