      "body" : "I think readlink as given is most elegant (and efficient), but I suggest <code>readlink -f $(which javac)</code>  - note the &#39;c&#39; in case there is a strange mix of JDK and JRE on the same machine. The JDK includes a compiler (javac) and a JRE does not. However if path is not correct, which will fail and you can try this: <code>find &#47;usr&#47;java -wholename &#39;*ava&#47;jdk*&#39; -prune</code> as I note in a comment below."
