      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "On Debian/Ubuntu if you have the <code>default-jdk</code> or <code>default-jre</code> packages installed, you can resolve the symbolic link <code>&#47;usr&#47;lib&#47;jvm&#47;default-java</code> that will point to the default version installed JDK or JRE according with your OS version: <code>readlink -f &#47;usr&#47;lib&#47;jvm&#47;default-java</code>"
